# `in` tests membership in a MAP; the right operand must be a map, not an array.
# Both compilers must reject this. tychoc0 used to fail open here -- it emitted a
# bogus map_*_has() call on the array (undeclared function / type-punned array as
# a map), which the C compiler then rejected. tychoc has always rejected it at the
# type level; this locks the parity.
fn main():
    a := [1, 2, 3]
    if 5 in a:
        print("x\n")
